title: Chocolate chip cookie ice cream

title: Chocolate mint creams

recipe: ['Mix all ingredients together.', "It's done."]

recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'Grease 12 muffin cups.', 'Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.', 'Cook and stir onion in hot oil until tender, about 5 minutes.', 'Stir chicken, salt, and pepper into onion; cook and stir until chicken is no longer pink in the center, about 5 minutes.', 'Pour milk into chicken mixture; bring to a boil.', 'Reduce heat to medium-low and simmer until chicken is no longer pink in the center, about 10 minutes.', 'Remove from heat and stir cheddar cheese into chicken mixture until melted.', 'Spoon chicken mixture into prepared muffin cups.', 'Bake in the preheated oven until a toothpick inserted into the center of a muffin comes']

title: Easy custard pie
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'In a medium bowl, mix together the flour, sugar and salt.', 'Cut in the butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.', 'Stir in the milk, egg and sour cream.', 'Pour into a 9 inch pie plate.', 'Bake in preheated oven for 30 minutes, or until a knife inserted into the center comes out clean.']

title: Ham with pineapple-orange mustard glaze
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 325f.', 'Place ham in roasting pan.', 'Mix brown sugar, mustard, ginger and cloves; spread over ham.', 'Bake 1 hour.', 'Reduce oven temperature to 325f.', 'Bake an additional 1 hour or until ham is cooked through.', 'Let stand 10 minutes before slicing.']

title: Dijon baked salmon
recipe: ['Heat oven to 400f.', 'Mix mustard, parsley and pepper.', 'Place fish in 13x9-inch baking dish sprayed with cooking spray; top with mustard mixture.', 'Bake 20 min.', 'Or until fish flakes easily with fork.']

title: Blueberry buckle
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees.', 'Grease a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.', 'In a large bowl, cream together butter and sugar.', 'Beat in eggs one at a time, then stir in vanilla.', 'Combine flour, baking powder and salt; stir into creamed mixture alternately with milk.', 'Fold in blueberries.', 'Spread batter into prepared pan.', 'In a small bowl, combine sugar, cinnamon and butter.', 'Sprinkle over batter.', 'Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.', 'Cool on a wire rack.']

title: Tomato & basil cottage cheese salad
recipe: ['Arrange tomatoes, cottage cheese and basil alternately on serving platter.', 'Sprinkle with parsley.']

title: Cheddar biscuits
recipe: ['Heat oven to 450 degrees f.', 'Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt in large bowl.', 'Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.', 'Stir in cheese.', 'Add enough ice water to make soft dough.', 'Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead 10 times.', 'Pat or roll to 3/4-inch thickness.', 'Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.', 'Place on baking sheet sprayed with cooking spray.', 'Bake 10 to 12 min.', 'Or until golden brown.']

title: Roasted ratatouille
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 400 degrees f (200 degrees c).', 'Place eggplant, zucchini, onion, and garlic in a large bowl.', 'Drizzle olive oil over vegetables and toss to coat.', 'Spread vegetables in a single layer on a baking sheet.', 'Roast in preheated oven until vegetables are tender and lightly browned, about 30 minutes.', 'Season with salt and pepper.']

title: Grilled onion wedges
recipe: ['Preheat grill to medium-high heat.', 'In a small bowl, combine the olive oil, garlic, salt and pepper.', 'Brush the onion wedges with the olive oil mixture and place on the grill.', 'Grill for about 5 minutes, turning once, until tender and lightly charred.']

title: Roasted tomato and mozzarella
recipe: ['Heat oven to 450f.', 'Toss tomatoes with oil and pepper in large bowl.', 'Spread onto rimmed baking sheet.', 'Bake 20 min.', 'Or until tomatoes are tender and golden brown, stirring after 10 min.', 'Sprinkle with cheese.']

title: Apple dumplings
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f (175 degrees c).', 'Grease a 9x13 inch baking dish.', 'In a large bowl, mix together the flour, sugar, salt, and cinnamon.', 'Cut in the butter until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.', 'Stir in the egg and milk.', 'Mix until a soft dough forms.', 'Turn out onto a lightly floured surface and knead lightly.', 'Roll out to 1/4 inch thickness.', 'Cut into squares.', 'Place squares into the prepared baking dish.', 'In a small bowl, mix together the brown sugar and cinnamon.', 'Sprinkle over the dumplings.', 'Bake in the preheated oven for 30 minutes, or until golden brown.']

title: Korean dipping sauce
recipe: ['Combine all ingredients in a small bowl.', 'Serve with grilled steak, pork, or chicken.']

title: Cinnamon cupcakes
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350f.', 'Line 12-cup muffin pan with paper liners.', 'Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon in bowl.', 'Beat butter and sugar in large bowl with electric mixer on medium speed until light and fluffy.', 'Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each addition.', 'Add vanilla; beat until well blended.', 'Add flour mixture alternately with milk, beating until well blended after each addition.', 'Spoon batter into prepared pan.', 'Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick inserted in centers comes out clean.', 'Cool in pan 5 minutes; remove to wire rack.', 'Cool completely.', 'Combine powdered sugar and milk in small bowl.', 'Drizzle over cupcakes.']

title: Chocolate chip granola bites
recipe: ['Preheat oven to 350 degrees f. line a baking sheet with parchment paper.', 'In a large bowl, combine oats, coconut, chocolate chips, and cinnamon.', 'In a small bowl, combine honey, brown sugar and vanilla.', 'Pour over oat mixture and stir until combined.', 'Using a small cookie scoop, drop mixture onto prepared baking sheet.', 'Bake for 10 minutes.', 'Remove from oven and let cool completely on baking sheet.', 'Store in an airtight container.']

title: Cheddar scones
recipe: ['Heat oven to 400f.', 'Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt in bowl.', 'Cut in butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.', 'Stir in cheese.', 'Combine milk and egg in another bowl; stir into flour mixture just until moistened.', 'Turn dough onto lightly floured surface; knead 10 times.', 'Pat or roll to 3/4-inch thickness.', 'Cut into 12 wedges.', 'Place on ungreased baking sheet.', 'Brush with milk.', 'Bake 10-12 minutes or until golden brown.']
